==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille in 1763. Originally called ''Horologium [[oscillitorium|Oscillitorium]]'' 
({{L.}} for "[[pendulum]] [[clock]]") to honor the [[Dutch]] astronomer and mathematician Christian Huygens, inventor of the pendulum clock.

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Horologium}}
'''Horologium'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] sky, said to resemble a [[pendulum]] [[clock]]. It lies between the constellations [[Fornax]] and [[Dorado]].

